But there's still an issue with `emitBX` and `emitBranch` which call `emitCondSkip` then `emitBXexit`/`emitExit` (which are large), then `patchSkip`, then another `emitExit`. With the new scheme, this still works because `patchSkip` patches the `b` to jump to whatever follows `emitBXexit`/`emitExit`.

